      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 12:58 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:zargon@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Zargon</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> Found <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009634.html"target="_blank">here</a> at the Everquest <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=General+Discussion&number=2"target="_blank">General Discussion Board</a><br><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><blockquote><br>Why is it while I'm crowd controlling multiple mobs and having to use both Enthrall and Entrance that when I go back thru to refresh the mezes Entrance (which is my level 34 mez) will not over ride my Enthrall (which is my level 16 one)? It gets pretty annoying trying to remember which was which, not to mention when I have a necro in the group who has to Screaming Terror something off of me. Please fix this if it is a bug.<br><font color=#a00000><br>The stacking of mez spells works as intended. They are not designed so that more powerful mez's overwrite weaker ones.<br><br>-Gordon<br></font></font></blockquote><br> </font> 
