      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 12:46 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:zargon@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Zargon</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> Found <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009659.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the Everquest <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=General+Discussion&number=2"target="_blank">General Discussion Board</a><blockquote><br><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><br>Why not make the mana vials expendable items that recover a certain amount of mana when consumed? The higher up the mana vial spell is, the more mana is regained by drinking the vial. You can keep down the abuse of this item by making it so they cannot be placed in any containers. That and the high level ones will be VERY expensive to make (4 rubies for the highest level mana vial).<br><font color=#a00000><br>I'm sorry, but we've ruled out creating "mana batteries". The greatest extent that we can implement a mana battery is done with the modulation rod (which eats hitpoints and is lore) and with your friendly neighborhood necromancer.<br><br>-Gordon</font></font></blockquote><br><br> </font> 
