    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Treant's Revenge on E'Ci</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>EverQuest_Server_Specific 
        [ 9:53 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:greebo@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Greebo</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <blockquote><font face="verdana" size=2 color=#050056>Wednesday night around 8:00pm CST on E'ci, a few members of our guild (Crimson Legacy) informed the rest of the guild that a GM-controlled druid and two Pegasi had come to the defense of the treants, which are always being slaughtered.  Fortunately at the time, my close wizard friend Vandna and I, a bard, were not busy, so we immediately teleported to North Karana and started running towards the treants to help protect them.  When we got there, we found an unkempt druid (sorry but I forgot his name) and the two pegasi, named <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/content/news/screenshots/PEGASI.jpg" target="_blank">Varrsselle and Terrevelle</a>.  The druid told us that he had been sent by Karana and that an 500 year old treant, Jival`Tos had been awakened from his centuries-old slumber to protect his younger bretheren.<br><br>The few evil-races that showed up were warned to leave or be killed.  Some left willingly, but others raised arms against these guardians of the treants and were swiftly killed.<br><br>We were told to protect the treants from those who would kill them and we would be rewarded for our efforts.  A few evil persons managed to kill a treant or two, but we tried to protect them as well as we were able by healing the treants or by helping the druid and the two Pegasi chase them off.<br><br>Eventually I was called forth by the druid and given a Serrated Bone Dirk for my efforts.  A druid, (I forget his name also, sorry) recieved a scimitar from the elder treant, <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/content/news/screenshots/JivalTos.jpg" target="_blank">Jival`Tos</a>.  The treant was then called back by Karana to return to his slumber.  The pegasi then flew around and gave a few items to some of those who had participated in helping protect the treants, as well as nuzzling the participants.  My partner Vandna received a Mithril Breastplate.  Briandaj, another guildmate, hit the jackpot when she received a Cloak of Shadows.  I was also given an Enamelled Black Mace from one of the pegasi before they were also called back to Karana.<br><br>/ooc All in all a fun GM event...  It was the first one that I had been to where I wasn't killed in the first 5 minutes... hehe  For the most part everyone role-played very well and I was glad to see that we didn't get a horde of level 50+ players all try to kill off all the NPC's.  A few evil characters did attack the NPC's, but with the possible exception of the druid that attacked the elder Treant, it was pretty appropriate as the attackers were evil races.<br><br>I've attached a couple of screenshots of the NPC's (minus the druid, I think I was in shock when he called me first to give me the dirk, so I didn't get a screenshot of him).</font></blockquote> </font> 
          <div align="right"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="http://eq.stratics.com/graphics/tikb.gif" width=5 height=5>&nbsp;<a href="#top">top</a></font></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <hr width="50%" align="center">
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
