  <tr> 
    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>New Possibility for Yelling</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b> 
        [ 10:34 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:raxon@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Raxon</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009115.html"target="_blank">this</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=General+Discussion&number=2" target="_blank">EverQuest General Discussion Boards</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" color=##050056 size=2>It was suggested a while ago that a person who uses the /yell command should have their name start flashing yellow, so its much easier to see which person it is.<br>You thought this was a good idea (and I agree) and you said you'd look into it. We never got that feature, and I was wondering what happened with it?<br></font><br><br><font face="Verdana" color="a00000" size=2>I do think that it's a good idea, and it's been forwarded to Rowyl with the other good UI enhancements that have been recommended. However, as it is part of a wish list, it's not something that I can give a periodic status update about.<br>-Gordon<br><br></font></blockquote><br><br> </font> 
