    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>More News on Velious</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b> 
        [ 10:23 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:raxon@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Raxon</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/009247.html" target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true">Official EverQuest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" color=##050056 size=2>Due to the fact that there will be no cap lift, no classes, or races, or anything new they will make one killer addition: story. Yep, Aradune said in some thread they are going to explain how Fironia (the women with very few garmets on the covers) exscapes from her chains in Kunark and hides away in Velious. <br><br>Velious is a 30+ area so I don't know if it is going to be a barbarian city like so many people say. There will be no teleport locations for either druids or wizards. There will be a boat from Erudin and maybe Kaladim or Ak'anon (since on the map there are two boats going towards Velious place, one from Odus and one from Faydwer). <br><br>Erudin already has a sign on the Port Authority that says to Qeynos and Velious. Hopefully there will be a god in Velious. Maybe Rallos Zek who has been recouperating from the invasion of earth (read the story if you don't know what I am talking about) with his creations. There is going to be high ice giants and dragons, don't know anything else.</font><br><br><font face="Verdana" color="a00000" size=2>It's still a bit early to say too much about Velious, but I did want to dispell some rumors:<br>1. There WILL be teleports into various locations in Velious (rumor has it they may work differently, however).<br><br>2. There is NO starting city in Velious.<br><br>3. There is NOT a barbarian city in Velious.<br><br>4. The target level range is 35-60.<br><br>Soon, as various previews in magazines as well as the official web page appear, we'll be able to tell you more of what IS in Velious <br><br>-Brad<br></font></blockquote> </font> 
