    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Official Warrior Tournament</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 6:07 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:greebo@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Greebo</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <blockquote><font face="verdana" size=2 color="#a000000">Greetings oh great warrior, I have traveled many days to reach you. Tales of your incredible deeds and great actions have reached my council, and to be honest, we are impressed with what we have learned. We watched in the shadows as you showed your bravery by defeating the evil dragons. We saw from a distance your unequal skill and courage when you banished gods from their own planes. Even Tunare herself has mentioned your name when she talks of the heroes of the Plane of Mortals.<br><br>We have heard of others who have similar accomplishments, and the gods have begun debate amongst themselves on who has created the ultimate champion. Of course, the dreaded Rallos Zek claims that his warriors would crush any that oppose his followers, but there are many that disagree. <br><br>Mithaniel Marr, in the plane of Valor, a place where the greatest tournaments are held, decreed that he would solve this dispute by holding a tournament of mortals that would forever answer the question on whose creation was superior. Those not in good standing with Mithaniel objected, stated that the event would be biased in his plane, and that neutral ground would be the only answer. <br><br>Being the Avatar of Truth, and bound by my code of honor to be forever unbiased regardless of race or profession, was summoned to this council and given this honorable quest to fulfill.<br><br>&#8220;Bring together the Myrmidons and Warlords, to a single place and a single time, and find the champion of mortals. Those that compete at the regional level and emerge victorious, grant them the title of &#8220;the Champion&#8221; by authorization of Rallos Zek. In the final event, where the heroes are brought together from all realms of the mortals, those that place 4th through 2nd shall be awarded the title of &#8220;the Myrmidon&#8221;, by authorization of the Tribunal. The winner of the final match, who has not lost to another mortal, under Authorization of Mithaniel Marr shall be awarded the title &#8220;the Warlord&#8221; and crowned the champion of Norrath.&#8221;<br><br>It had been many ages since I had been requested to accomplish such a quest.  Rules would have to be fair, for even Cazic Thule, in his blindness, would be able to see if the event would be biased twords one of the gods creations. From Gnome to Ogre, and Human to Iksar, all would have to be equal.<br><br>Some gods had given artifacts to faithful followers, that placed them above most mortals, clearly an advantage that would need to be dismissed. Therefore, let it be known that all Artifacts will be banished from this event.<br><br>Several of the gods had blessed their children into riches with great armies, which could afford the wealth of many items and equipment. This would advantage some races over others, which could not be involved in the event. Therefore, let it be known that all activatable items will be banished from this event. Of course, great warrior, you may wear the items that have the special abilities imbedded into them, just not use those items against another player in the forms of spells or potions or pumice or effects.<br><br>Finally the use of weapons was agreed upon, and weapons based of trickery and deceit were banished from the event by Mithaniel. Rallos disagreed stating that a true warrior uses any weapon or equipment to his advantage, and they argued.  Finally my recommendation pleased them both, and these weapons were banished from the primary hand of the warrior, only to be used in the offhand. Therefore, let it be known, that all weapons of deceit (weapons with a delay value of 15 or lower) shall only be allowed in the offhand of the competitors.<br><br>Leave your gold pouch in the bank, for no entry fee shall be requested or accepted in this event. Seek the knowledge of the gods for the time and place of regiona (Server) tournaments before the greatest are gathered to one spot (test server) for the final event.  This is my quest, and my message to you my champion. I hope you accept this quest as well as a personal goal to come and compete at the event of the gods. If the challenge is too great, I assure you that your god shall forgive you, for only the bravest and best need step forward.<br><br>Fare well, I hope we meet again.<br><br><br>Server Tournaments<br><br>Fri Sept 1st, 2000<br>Xegony 6pm PST<br>E Marr 6pm PST<br>Quellious 6pm PST<br><br>Sat Sept 2nd, 2000<br>Vallon Zek 4pm PST<br>Innoruuk 8pm PST<br>The Rathe 7pm PST<br>7th Hammer 5pm PST<br><br>Sun Sept 3rd, 2000<br>T Thule 6pm PST<br>Lanys 430pm PST<br>Veeshan 6pm PST<br>T Marr 3pm PST<br><br>Tue Sept 5th, 2000<br>Bertox 7pm PST<br>Fennin 5pm PST<br>E`Ci 4pm PST<br>Sol Ro 5pm PST<br>Rodcet 6pm PST<br><br>Wed Sept 6th, 2000<br>Rallos 5pm PST<br>Karana 4pm PST<br>Nameless 6pm PST<br><br>Thur Sept 7th, 2000<br>Luclin 7pm PST<br>Torv 6pm PST<br>Saryrn 5pm PST<br>Tribunal 4pm PST<br><br>Fri Sept 8th, 2000<br>Brell 7pm PST<br>M Marr 4pm PST<br>M Thule 5pm PST<br><br>Sat Sept 9th, 2000<br>Prexus 5pm PST<br><br>TBA<br>Tallon Zek<br>Tunare<br>Bristle<br>Druzzil<br>Povar<br>C Thule<br><br>Sun Sept 10, 2000<br>Final Event - Test Server<br><br>All TBA's will be announced shortly<br><br>Lady Daegarmo<br>Online Events Coordinator<br>Verant Interactive</font></blockquote> </font> 
