    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Guild List for Guild Leaders</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 1:46 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/007771.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#050056">Here's a suggestion for the UI - allow the Leader of a guild to get a list of all chars which have the Guild Tag, whether logged on or not.<br><br>I have difficulty sometimes keeping track of who joined, who left, and who's cancelled accounts, even though we have a website.<br><br>Could this be implemented?<br><br><font color="#a00000">The problem here is that the server doesn't keep a list of who's in a guild.<br><br>We have a list of guilds, and each character record has an index into that list.<br><br>With thousands of character per server it's not feasable to search the entire database to generate a list of who's in the guild.<br><br>While I agree this would be a nice feature, it's just not gonna happen. Sorry.<br><br>-Rowyl</font></font></blockquote> </font> 
