    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>A Few UI Suggestions</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 1:25 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008621.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#050056">Heres a few suggestions that occurred to me while playing. Apologies if they have been mentioned before.<br><br>1. If you have a wheel-mouse, how about enabling the wheel so that it can be used to scroll the text window? It would need to be pretty speedy, so I would suggest scrolling by page, not by line.<br><br>2. When healing yourself, would it be possible to stop your health bar shooting up and then settling back down to a lower value?<br><br>3. Could there be an 'exchange and bank' button on the bank screen that automatically transfers all your money to your bank vault and changes it into the highest value coin, so avoiding the rather laborious multiple-clicking. I would not consider this to be anti-roleplay because it is what you would ask a bank cashier to do anyway.<br><br>4. It would be really really good if there was an option to switch off the ability to right-click on a player to examine them. It is useful and fast to right-click to con MOBs, and when a player is in the way it is both annoying and time consuming, especially in a battle situation.<br><br>5. Pretty low priority, but it would be nice if containers remembered where they opened on screen. I would imagine the simplest solution to implement would be to store a location for each inventory slot, rather than for each container. If a container is in a particular inventory slot, that container uses the slots stored position when it opens. If another container is switched into that same slot, then it would use the same location.  Locations would be updated when a container is moved around the screen.<br><br><font color="#a00000">I will look into 1, 2, 4, and 5, I doubt number 3 is going to happen.<br><br>-Rowyl</font></font></blockquote> </font> 
          <div align="right"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="http://eq.stratics.com/graphics/tikb.gif" width=5 height=5>&nbsp;<a href="#top">top</a></font></div>
        </div>
