    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Guild Bank Accounts</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 11:21 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008296.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#050056">Since Norrath has those wonderful magic banks that can teleport goods and cash across the world faster than an evac, how about adding another NPC to the Major banks of Norrath? the Guild Joint Account Banker!<br><br>Basically, any guild member can deposit money and items into the special bank account to be withdrawn by other guild members.<br><br>Or the guild leader can set it to 'deposit only' for regular members, with only officers able to withdraw.<br><br>I think this would take away a good chunk of the desire for 'Guild Halls'<br><br>Implementation might not be easy... if the current bank accounts are hard-linked to the character, account data not specifically linked to a specific character might be difficult to do. but since it would be limited to 8 slots and cash for the whole guild it shouldn't take to much data storage space, and just attach it to the guild leaders account.<br><br><font color="#a00000">>>>Because it would take work.<br><br>Every change takes work, it's just a question of how much work and whether or not the benefits of the change are worth diverting the manpower from other things that they could be working on, and whether the suggested changes are consistant with the game world.<br><br>I think that the suggestion does meet the "consistant with the game world" qualification, but am not sure that it would apply well to the others. Guilds do not currently exist as an entity, but rather as an entry within each character file. In order to implement this, guilds would have to be converted to be an entity all their own. Secondly, restrictions for nodrop and lore items would have to be implemented in ways that would only apply to guild banks.<br><br>It's not just work, but a substantial amount of manpower that's probably better served elsewhere at present. We won't rule it out completely though.<br><br>-Gordon</font></font></blockquote><br><br>Talk about this <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=7,8,9,10,11&Board=eqwestwood&Number=376849&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5"target="_blank">here</a> </font> 
