    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Partisan Pack Follow-up</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 10:53 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008775.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#a00000">Hello all,<br><br>There was another thread that someone started in regards to an item known as the Partisan Pack, a combinable quest bag given out by an NPC. Since that thread has gone a little off-topic, I thought the follow-up which I promised would do better in a new one.<br><br>Apparently in the last patch, the item changed from a 10-slot container to a 6-slot container, causing some to lose item stored in slots 7-10. <br><br>Since people have grown accustomed to storing items within quest-bags, a change of this type should have been pre-announced, in order to avoid item loss. We do indeed apologize for the change being made without that advance notice. We have logged data for any items that were lost by the change, so you may contact a GM for assistance.<br><br>-Gordon</font></blockquote><br><br>Talk about this <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=7,8,9,10,11&Board=eqwestwood&Number=376820&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5"target="_blank">here</a> </font> 
