    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Gordon Answers Some Questions</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 10:46 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008845.html"Target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"Target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#050056">1. Camping. Why couldn't the "long portion" of the camp be put at the OTHER end of the camp? Perhaps the NPC needs time to "craft" the quest item and changes in some way to show that they are ready to give the reward. Let the other items spawn almost continuously, and people would NEED to camp anything but the reward PC. <br><br><font color="#a00000">It's a doable idea, but wouldn't this be just a camp by another name? Whether I'm camping a creature that I want to kill, or one I want to talk to, it's still a camp. In this case, I can see 20 people standing around an NPC waiting for him to "be ready" and<br>fighting over who can hand him the items fastest. <br><br><font color="#050056">2. Are there currently any suits of armor that give some "hidden" effect or bonus by virtue of wearing the entire suit? <br><br><font color="#a00000">No, there are not. It's a good idea though that might have some application for later implementation or future products.<br><br><font color="#050056">3. Are there currently any weapons in the game that have any "hidden" effect? <br><br><font color="#a00000">Not really. What an item can do is expressly stated upon it. We do have some plans for more cursed weaponry in the future, of course we just might have to be creative to "hide" the effect of the curse.<br><br><font color="#050056">4. If the answer to 2 and/or 3 is "no", are there any plans to add this feature to the game? <br><br><font color="#a00000">See above.<br><br><font color="#050056">5. You once said that GZ was going to conduct some tests with the wizard's spells vs. the other caster classes. Have these been completed? <br><br><font color="#a00000">Actually I believe that Brad said that, and it is indeed our opinion that offensive power is appropriate for the class.<br><br><font color="#050056">6. Why, exactly, was the definition of the wizard class changed on the everquest.com page under the classes section? <br><br><font color="#a00000">What change and when was it made? To my knowledge, it has read what it reads now since release. I believe that there was a change at one time in the beta period where it was changed from "damage" to "magical damage", but that's all I believe happened. Was there something else?<br><br><font color="#050056">7. Are there any plans to introduce items that directly influence/enhance trade skills? (Gnomish Jeweler's Loupe, Dwarven Smith's Hammer, Elven Sewing Needle, etc.) <br><br><font color="#a00000">Do you mean items that allow you to make better items with trades? It's a good idea, but we no firm plans in that direction. <br><br><font color="#050056">8. Why, since dwarves in fantasy literature (and even in EQ) are the finest smiths in all the realms, is there no ore in Kaladim? It even has a mine. <br><br><font color="#a00000">Good question. There's no ore in Kaladim? Hmmm, I'll check into that to see if it was a design or an oversight.<br><br><font color="#050056">9. Why can't enchanters be given a high-level illusion that allows them to change into the nearest ANIMATE object? <br><br><font color="#a00000">Races are a component of faction, and you adopt whatever race-faction you emulate.  There's a lot of special case-coding to handle the animate races that players currently emulate. Opening that up to nearly everything else would be extremely problematic, if not impossible.<br><br><font color="#050056">10. Are there any plans to introduce a spell or item that absorbs magic directed at the wielder, perhaps converting it directly into mana/hit points? <br><br><font color="#a00000">There is already a bard song that has a damage shield that absorbs magical damage.  There's also a cleric "reverse damage shield" that heals anyone that hits the target.  That's the extent of what we have, and nothing new along these lines are planned.<br><br><font color="#050056">11. Are there any plans to introduce a spell or item that REFLECTS spells back at the caster? <br><br><font color="#a00000">No.<br><br><font color="#050056">12. Why can't the monk-only weapons that look like gloves be worn on the hands, and add directly to the ATTACK stat instead of requiring them to be 1h blunt? <br><br><font color="#a00000">Items cannot be set to use hand-to-hand skill, and combat can't go to an "equipment" slot to get combat statistics.<br><br><font color="#050056">13. If Verant doesn't like "spoiler sites", then why are there no spell descriptions anywhere in the game?<br><br><font color="#a00000">I think that you've answered your own question. We don't like spoilers. We'd prefer people figure these things out on their own and maintain their own knowledge-base. <br><br><font color="#050056">14. Will players ever be able to construct golems? (A.k.a. summon a temporary "golem-type" pet through some complicated quest) <br><br><font color="#a00000">We could certainly, by use of trade skill or quest, award an item that summoned a pet of any particular type, however we have no plans to do that at present.<br><br><font color="#050056">15. Necros can charm the undead; enchanters can charm...well...everything. Will Magicians ever have the ability/spell to charm elementals or other summoned creatures?<br><br><font color="#a00000">No, we have no plans along these lines at present.<br><br><font color="#050056">16. Are there any plans for an expansion geared toward the 10 - 30 range of player rather than the higher levels? <br><br><font color="#a00000">Velious is geared towards a higher level-range, however Kunark has support for all level ranges. <br><br>With Velious, the thinking is that there is already plenty of content to support the continually migrating portion of the customer-base that is in the 10-30 range. <br><br>I'm unable to talk about any post-Velious plans at this time.<br><br><font color="#050056">17. The Trackers' Water Extractor - This is currently broken, is it not? The purification tablets do not seem to exist, and the NPC that mentions them won't respond.<br><br><font color="#a00000">I inquired about this time time back, when Kunark first launched, and it was verified at the time that the tablets do exist. If I need to check into it further, please let me know.<br><br><font color="#050056">18. Bandages vs. Aloe Swatches vs. Maneater Plant Salve vs. Tailored Silk Bandages: Is there any difference other than price i.e. More healing, faster healing, etc.<br><br><font color="#a00000">No difference at this time.<br><br><font color="#050056">19. Are there any plans to give clerics any type of special ability that is tied to whatever deity they worship?<br><br><font color="#a00000">No, there are currently no plans along these lines. However, there are plans and implemented pieces of deity-specific quests that return deity-specific rewards.<br><br><font color="#050056">20. Are there any races and/or classes that you, personally, would like to see added to the game?<br><br><font color="#a00000">If we added a warrior/wizard hybrid, could we call him a "fire fighter"?<br><br>-Gordon</font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></blockquote><br><br>Talk about this <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=7,8,9,10,11&Board=eqwestwood&Number=376828&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5"target="_blank">here</a> </font> 
          <div align="right"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="http://eq.stratics.com/graphics/tikb.gif" width=5 height=5>&nbsp;<a href="#top">top</a></font></div>
        </div>
      </div>
