      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Stratics_Network_Announcement 
        [ 6:08 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:greebo@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Greebo</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <blockquote><font face="verdana" size=2 color=#050056><p><a href="http://www.stratics.com">Stratics</a> is seeking energetic and articulate volunteers to help update its central site, which is currently under redesign and refocus for a grand reopening sometime next month. This new site will focus on the MMORPG industry as a whole, offering looks at a wide range of games in development as well as news regarding the companies behind those games, and other special features. <br><p>Those selected will gain the privilege to work with a professional news staff. The writing samples can be used from which to start building portfolios, will look good on any business resume, and can help make a nice entry into the gaming/media industry. Applicants should possess the following qualities:<br><ul><li>Ability to write interesting, non-fiction, industry related pieces</li><br><li>Demonstrate editorial skills such as grammar, spelling, and proofreading</li><br><li>Proficiency with basic HTML</li><br><li>General knowledge of the gaming industry</li><br><li>Ability to research articles using both the internet and printed media</li><br><li>Approximately 10-15 hours available per week to write articles and assist with site updates</li></ul><br><p>If interested, please email <a href="mailto:xander@stratics.com">Xander</a> with a brief description of your background, why you wish to be considered for the position, and (most importantly) a <b>writing sample</b>. <i>Note: All writing samples must be pasted into the body of the email or submitted as a URL posted on the web somewhere. No attached files will be accepted</i>. </font></blockquote> </font> 
