    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>End of Heroes of Valor's Month Long Events</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b> 
        [ 5:09 PM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:wowous@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Wowous</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <font face="verdana" size=2><br>From Ignitz Gemcaller, The Guildmaster of Heroes of Valor:<br><P><br><blockquote><font face="verdana" size=2 color = #050056><br>I would like to officially announce the end of the Heroes of Valor month long events calender. All this past month, on each Friday, we planned and held an event and for this last one we decided it was time for our Elder Paladin in the guild, Braxus Silverhand, to receive the second of the Paladin Holy Swords, Soulfire.<br><br>The call went out at 7pm CST for friends to come and join us in the northern portion of the Newbie Area in West Freeport. Within the hour we had almost 20 people there to help take Sir Lucan down. The pull was made, the battle was joined, and within a minute, Lucan, both his human and skeletal form, fell. The Testimony of Truth was looted and the Brilliant Sword of Faith was brought forth out of Northern Freeport.<br><br>We made haste to Southern Karana and found our way into the dungeon of<br>Infected Paw. Many a gnoll sought to prevent us from attaining our goal but not a single one succeeded. Finally, we found ourselves in the jail area of the dungeon, where we stood in front of Brother Hayle and handed him all the items he requested in order to bless Braxus with Soulfire. In the end, Braxus stood before us, the firey blade in hand, and smile as wide as the world of Norrath on his face.<br><br>But we did not stop there no. The next morning we sought Soulfire once again for another Paladin in our guild, Sanain Fyrestarr. While we did not have as many people there for this Lucan slaying, we did manage to kill him and Sanain received his Soulfire as well.<br><br>For a guild as small as the Heroes of Valor this is truly a magnificent feat and I wish to thank everyone who participated in both slayings. A special thanks goes out to Azoth and Lile, both of whom were there for both slayings, even though they were not part of our guild.<br></FONT></BLOCKQUOTE><br><br>Wow! What a great accomplishment for a small guild!<br></FONT> </font> 
          <div align="right"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><img src="http://eq.stratics.com/graphics/tikb.gif" width=5 height=5>&nbsp;<a href="#top">top</a></font></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <hr width="50%" align="center">
