    <td><font color="050056" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Gambling In Everquest</b></font> 
      <div><font color="#660000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>Official_EverQuest_Forums 
        [ 10:53 AM EDT ] -</b></font><font color="ff0000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> 
        <a href="mailto:ogamok@stratics.com?subject=EQNews">Ogamok</a></font> 
        <div><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> I found this <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008624.html"target="_blank">here</a> on the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"target="_blank">Official Everquest Forums</a><br><br><blockquote><font face="Verdana" size=2 color="#a00000">Though these are good ideas and we have given tremendous thought to them, we elected a while back not to pursue gambling within the game. Frankly, the biggest hurdle is a legal one. Since people are selling in-game items and platinum for real-world cash, it would allow someone to convert their gambling winnings to cash, and cash into a gambling medium. That would leave it open to being argued that gambling in EverQuest is gambling in the real world.<br><br>Though we are leaving the option open for future products, and looking into the legal issues involved, it's not a possibility for EverQuest going forward.<br><br>-Gordon</font></blockquote><br><br>Talk about this <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=7,8,9,10,11&Board=eqwestwood&Number=376125&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5"target="_blank">here</a> </font> 
